lemma prop40rtl :
  assumes "¬ dependvar f M 0"
  and "¬ dependvar g M 0"
  and "finite A"
  and "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A
     ∧ alloccurringstates s (fin p) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦mu (and' g (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0))))⟧ M e"
  apply (simp add: assms(3))
  apply (rule allI)
proof
  fix S'
  from assms(4) obtain p s' where assum1 : "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A
     ∧ alloccurringstates s (fin p) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e" by auto
  assume assum2: "⟦g⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∩ 
    (⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'}) ⊆ S' "
  have inS' : "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A
     ∧ insert s (set (map target p)) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ s' ∈ S' ⟶ s ∈ S'"
    apply (induct p arbitrary : s; simp)
  proof
    fix t p s
    assume assum3 : "(⋀s. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ target ` set p ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ s' ∈ S' ⟶ s ∈ S')"
    assume assum4 : "s = source t ∧ t ∈ transition M ∧ validfinpath M (target t) p s' ∧ action t ∈ A ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ target t ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ target ` set p ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ s' ∈ S'"
    hence "target t ∈ S'" using assum3 by auto
    hence "(source t, action t, target t) ∈ transition M ∧ target t ∈ S'" using assum4 splittransition by metis
    hence "source t ∈ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'}" using assum4 by blast
    moreover have "source t ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e" using assum4 by auto
    moreover from this have "source t ∈ ⟦g⟧ M (newenvironment e S')" using notdependshiftdown assms(2) by metis
    ultimately show "source t ∈ S'" using assum2 by auto
  qed
  have "validfinpath M s p s' ⟶ s' ∈ insert s (set (map target p))" by (induct p arbitrary: s; simp)
  hence "s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e" using assum1 by auto
  hence "s' ∈ ⟦g⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∧ s' ∈ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S')" by (simp add: assms(1) assms(2) notdependshiftdown)
  thus "s ∈ S'" using assum1 assum2 inS' by auto
qed

lemma prop40ltrinbetween :
  assumes "¬dependvar f M 0"
  and "¬dependvar g M 0"
  and "finite A"
  shows "s ∈ ((transformer (and' g (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0)))) M e)^^n){} ⟶
  (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A
     ∧ alloccurringstates s (fin p) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e)"
  apply (induct n arbitrary : s)
  apply (simp)
proof
  fix n s
  let ?f = "and' g (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0)))"
  let ?S' = "(transformer ?f M e ^^ n) {}"
  assume assum1 : "⋀s. s ∈ ?S'
    ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A ∧ alloccurringstates s (fin p) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e)"
  let ?S'' = "(transformer ?f M e ^^ Suc n) {}"
  assume assum2 : "s ∈ ?S''"
  hence splitand : "s ∈ ⟦g⟧ M (newenvironment e ?S') 
    ∧ (s ∈ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e ?S') ∨ (∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S'))" by (simp add: transformer_def assms(3) del: Diamond.simps)
  hence ing : "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e" using notdependshiftdown assms by metis
  from splitand have "s ∈ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e ?S') ∨ (∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S')" by auto
  moreover {
    assume assum3 : "s ∈ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e ?S')"
    from assum3 have "s ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e)" by (metis assms(1) notdependshiftdown)
    hence "validfinpath M s [] s ∧ s ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e) ∧ (action ` set [] ⊆ A) ∧ s ∈ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e) ∧ (target ` set []) ⊆ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e)" using ing by simp
    hence "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A ∧ s ∈ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e) ∧ (target ` set p) ⊆ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e)" by blast
  }
  moreover {
    assume "∃s' a. a ∈ A ∧ (s, a, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S'"
    then obtain s' a where assum3 : "a ∈ A ∧ (s, a, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S'" by auto
    hence "∃p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A
      ∧ (s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ target ` set p ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e)" using assum1 by auto
    then obtain p s'' where tail : "validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A
      ∧ (s' ∈ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e) ∧ target ` set p ⊆ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e))" by auto
    let ?p = "(s, a, s') # p"
    have "source (s, a, s') = s ∧ (s, a, s') ∈ transition M ∧ validfinpath M (target (s, a, s')) p s''" using assum3 tail by simp
    hence "validfinpath M s ?p s''" by auto
    hence "validfinpath M s ?p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e) ∧ (action ` set ?p ⊆ A) ∧ 
      s ∈ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e) ∧ target ` set ?p ⊆ (⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e)" using assum3 ing tail by simp
    hence "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A 
      ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e ∧ target ` set p ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e" by blast
  }
  ultimately show "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A
      ∧ alloccurringstates s (fin p) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e" by (simp; blast)
qed

lemma prop40ltr :
  fixes M :: "('a, 's) lts"
  assumes "s ∈ ⟦mu (and' g (or (f) (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0))))⟧ M e"
  and "¬dependvar f M 0"
  and "¬dependvar g M 0"
  and "finite (UNIV :: 's set)"
  and "finite A"
  shows "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' 
        ∧ s' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e) 
        ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A 
        ∧ alloccurringstates s (fin p) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e"
proof-
  have "mono (transformer (and' g (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0)))) M e)" by (rule monotonicitynotdependcoro(1); simp add: assms notdepends)
  hence "s ∈ ((transformer (and' g (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0)))) M e)^^(card (UNIV :: 's set))){}" using assms(1) assms(4) transformer_eq_mu by auto 
  thus ?thesis using prop40ltrinbetween assms(2) assms(3) assms(5) by metis
qed

proposition proposition40 :
  fixes M :: "('a, 's) lts"
  assumes "¬ dependvar f M 0"
  and "¬ dependvar g M 0"
  and "finite (UNIV :: 's set)"
  and "finite A"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦mu (and' g (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0))))⟧ M e = 
    (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A  
      ∧ alloccurringstates s (fin p) ⊆ ⟦shiftdown g 0⟧ M e)"
  apply (rule iffI)
  apply (rule prop40ltr; simp add: assms)
  apply (rule prop40rtl; simp add: assms)
  done

lemma invariantApath : 
  assumes "¬ dependvar f M 0"
  and "S' ⊆ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'}"
  and "s ∈ S' ∩ {s. ∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧  alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A}"
  shows "∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S' ∩ {s'. ∄p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A}"
proof-
  have "s ∈ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'}" using assms(2) assms(3) by auto
  hence "s ∈ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∨  (∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S')" using assms(2) by auto
  moreover have "s ∉ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S')"
    apply (rule ccontr)
    apply (simp)
  proof-
    assume "s ∈ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S')"
    hence "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e" using assms(1) notdependshiftdown by metis
    hence "validfinpath M s [] s ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧  alloccurringactions (fin []) ⊆ A" by auto
    thus False using assms(3) by blast
  qed
  ultimately have "∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'" by auto
  then obtain act s' where assum1 : "act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'" by auto
  have "∄p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e) ∧ (set (map action p) ⊆ A)"
    apply (rule ccontr)
    apply (simp)
  proof-
    assume "∃p s''. s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A"
    then obtain p s'' where "s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A" by auto
    hence "validfinpath M s ((s, act, s')#p) s'' ∧ s'' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e) ∧ alloccurringactions (fin ((s, act, s')#p)) ⊆ A" using assum1 by simp
    thus False using assms(3) by blast
  qed
  thus ?thesis using assum1 by auto
qed

lemma theorem21generalizedltr : 
  assumes "¬ dependvar f M 0"
  and "finite A"
  and "s ∈ ⟦nu (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0)))⟧ M e"
  shows "((∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A ∧ s' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e)) ∨
    (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧  alloccurringactions (inf p) ⊆ A))"
proof-
  have "∃S'. S' ⊆ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'} ∧ s ∈ S'" using assms(2) assms(3) by (simp del: Diamond.simps)
  then obtain S' where assum1 : "S' ⊆ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'} ∧ s ∈ S'" by auto
  have "(∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e) ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A) ⟹  (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ (∀n. action (p n) ∈ A))"
    apply (rule successorlemma)
  proof-
    assume assum2 : "∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A"
    let ?S' = "S' ∩ {s'. ∄p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e) ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A}" 
    have "(∀s'. (s' ∈ ?S' ⟶ (∃t. source t = s' ∧ action t ∈ A ∧ t ∈ transition M ∧ target t ∈ ?S')))"
      apply (rule allI)
    proof
      fix s
      assume assum3 : "s ∈ ?S'"
      have "¬ dependvar f M 0 ⟹ S' ⊆ ⟦f⟧ M (newenvironment e S') ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S'} ⟹ s ∈ S' ∩ {s. ∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ set (map action p) ⊆ A} ⟹ ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ S' ∩ {s'. ∄p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A}" using invariantApath by simp
      hence "∃s'' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s'') ∈ (transition M) ∧ s'' ∈ ?S'" using assum1 assum3 assms(1) by simp
      thus "∃t. source t = s ∧ action t ∈ A ∧ t ∈ transition M ∧ target t ∈ ?S'" by auto
    qed
    moreover have "s ∈ ?S'" using assum1 assum2 by auto
    ultimately show "s ∈ ?S' ∧ (∀s'. (s' ∈ ?S' ⟶ (∃t. source t = s' ∧ action t ∈ A ∧ t ∈ transition M ∧ target t ∈ ?S')))" by simp
  qed
  thus ?thesis by (simp only: image_subset_iff alloccurringmap.simps; auto)
qed

lemma theorem21generalizedrtl : 
  assumes "¬ dependvar f M 0"
  and "finite A"
  and "(∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A ∧ s' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e)) ∨
     (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧  alloccurringactions (inf p) ⊆ A)" 
  shows "s ∈ ⟦nu (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0)))⟧ M e"
  apply (simp add: assms(2) del: Diamond.simps)
  apply (subst notdependshiftdown)
  apply (simp add: assms(1))
  apply (rule exI)
proof
  let ?S' = "{s. (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (set (map action p) ⊆ A) ∧ s' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e)) ∨
              (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ image action (range p) ⊆ A)}"
  show "s ∈ ?S'" using assms(3) by simp
  show "?S' ⊆ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S'}"
  proof
    fix s
    assume "s ∈ ?S'"
    moreover {  
      assume "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ set (map action p) ⊆ A"
      then obtain p s' where assum1 : "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ set (map action p) ⊆ A" by auto
      have "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ set (map action p) ⊆ A ⟹ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ (∃p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ set (map action p) ⊆ A))"
        apply (induct p arbitrary : s)
        apply (simp_all add: validfinpath.cases)
      proof-
        fix t p
        (*assum2 only needed for base case?*)
        assume assum3 : "t ∈ transition M ∧ validfinpath M (target t) p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ action t ∈ A ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A"
        hence "(source t, action t, target t) ∈ transition M ∧ (validfinpath M (target t) p s' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ action t ∈ A ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A)" using splittransition by metis
        thus "source t ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (source t, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ (∃p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∧ action ` set p ⊆ A))" by blast
      qed
      hence "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S'}" using assum1 by auto
    }
    moreover {
      assume "∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ (∀n. action (p n) ∈ A)"
      then obtain p where assum1 : "validinfpath M s p ∧ (∀n. action (p n) ∈ A)" by auto
      hence "s = source (p 0) ∧ (p 0) ∈ transition M ∧ action (p 0) ∈ A ∧ validinfpath M (target (p 0)) (suffix (Suc 0) p) ∧ (∀n. action ((suffix (Suc 0) p) n) ∈ A)" by (simp add: validinfpath_def)
      hence "(s, action (p 0), target (p 0)) ∈ transition M  ∧ action (p 0) ∈ A ∧ validinfpath M (target (p 0)) (suffix (Suc 0) p) ∧ (∀n. action ((suffix (Suc 0) p) n) ∈ A)" by simp
      hence "∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧  (∃p. validinfpath M s' p ∧ (∀n. action (p n) ∈ A))" by blast
      hence "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S'}" using assum1 by blast
   }
   ultimately show "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e ∪ {s. ∃s' act. act ∈ A ∧ (s, act, s') ∈ transition M ∧ s' ∈ ?S'}" by blast
 qed
qed

lemma theorem21generalized :  
  assumes "¬ dependvar f M 0"
  and "finite A"
  shows "(s ∈ ⟦nu (or f (Diamond (Acts A) (var 0)))⟧ M e) =
  ((∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ alloccurringactions (fin p) ⊆ A ∧ s' ∈ (⟦shiftdown f 0⟧ M e)) ∨ 
  (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ alloccurringactions (inf p) ⊆ A))"
  apply (rule iffI)
  apply (rule theorem21generalizedltr; simp add: assms)
  apply (rule theorem21generalizedrtl; simp add: assms)
  done

lemma negformula [simp] : "(s ∈ ⟦neg f⟧ M e) = (s ∉ ⟦f⟧ M e)" by simp

lemma notoccursfin [simp] : "action ` set p ⊆ -α⇩f = (¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p))" by auto

lemma notoccursinf [simp] : "action ` range p ⊆ -α⇩f = (¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p))" by auto

theorem theorem21 :
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ finite (-B)"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (Box (Acts (-B)) ff)) (Diamond (Acts (-α⇩f)) (var 0)))))⟧ M e 
    = (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p)"
  apply (subst negformula)
proof-
  have "∀s. s ∈ ⟦Diamond ρ (nu (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (Box (Acts (-B)) ff)) (Diamond (Acts (-α⇩f)) (var 0))))⟧ M e 
    = (∃p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p )"
    apply (subst Diamondmatch)
    apply (simp add: assms del: formulasemantics.simps)
  proof
    let ?A = "λs'. s' ∈ ⟦nu (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (Box (Acts (- B)) ff)) (Diamond (Acts (- α⇩f)) (var 0)))⟧ M e"
    let ?B = "λs'.  (∃p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s'' ∨ enabled M s'' α⇩e)) ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s' p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p))"
    let ?C = "λs'. (∃ p. freeuntiloccurrence p α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s' B p)"
    have res1 : "∀s'. ?A s' = ?B s'"
      apply (subst theorem21generalized; simp add: assms notoccursnotdepends Boxcomplement_locked Diamond_enabled del: Diamond.simps Box.simps Diamond_eq_exist Box_eq_forall occurssimps)
      apply auto
      done
    have res2: "∀s'. ?C s' = ?B s'" by (subst freeuntiloccurrenceprogressing_lockedenabled; simp)
    have "∀s'. ?A s' = ?C s'" by (subst res2; subst res1; auto)
    thus "⋀s. (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ match ρ p ∧ s' ∈ ⟦nu (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (Box (Acts (-B)) ff)) (Diamond (Acts (-α⇩f)) (var 0)))⟧ M e) = (∃p. match ρ p ∧ (∃p' s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ freeuntiloccurrence p' α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s' B p'))" by blast    
  qed
  thus "(s ∉ ⟦Diamond ρ (nu (formula.or (formula.or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (Box (Acts (- B)) ff)) (Diamond (Acts (- α⇩f)) (var 0))))⟧ M e) = (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p)" by blast
qed

lemma lemma50 : 
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ finite (α⇩_el a)"
  and "¬dependvar (φ_off a) M 0"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (and' (φ_off a) (var 0))) (Diamond (Acts ((α⇩_el a) -α⇩f)) (var 0)))⟧ M (newenvironment e S') 
    = (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ 
        ((enabled M s' α⇩e) ∨ (s' ∈ S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) ∨ (∃s'' a'. a' ∈ ((α⇩_el a) - α⇩f) ∧ (s', a', s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ S')) ))"
  apply (subst Diamondmatch)
  apply (simp add: assms enabled_def)
  apply (subst matchstaract)
  apply (simp del: Diamond.simps add: assms)
  apply (subst notdependshiftdown; simp add: assms)
  apply meson
  done 
                                 
lemma occursactionorstate : 
  assumes "∀s'. ((∃p' s''. validfinpath M s' p' s'' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p') ∧ locked M B s'') ⟶ s' ∈ S')"
  and "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s' ∧ (occurs A (fin p) ∨ occursstate S'' s (fin p))"
  shows "∃p' s'. validfinpath M s p' s' ∧ ((s' ∈ S' ∩ S'') ∨ (∃a s''. (s', a, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ a ∈ A ∧ s'' ∈ S'))"
proof-
  have "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s' ⟹ (∀i < length p. source (p!i) ∈ S')"
    apply rule
  proof
    fix i
    assume assum1 : "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s'"
    assume "i < length p"
    hence "validfinpath M (source (p!i)) (drop i p) s' ∧ locked M B s'" using assum1 by auto
    moreover have "¬ occurs α⇩f (fin (drop i p))" unfolding notoccursfin using assum1 set_drop_subset by fastforce
    ultimately show "source (p!i) ∈ S'" using assms by blast
  qed
  hence "∀i < length p. source (p!i) ∈ S'" using assms by auto
  hence "source ` set p ⊆ S'" by (metis image_subsetI in_set_conv_nth)
  moreover have "s' ∈ S'"
  proof-
    have "validfinpath M s' [] s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin []) ∧ locked M B s'" using assms by auto
    thus "s' ∈ S'" using assms by metis
  qed
  ultimately have "insert s' (set (map source p)) ⊆ S'" by simp
  moreover have "validfinpath M s p s' ⟶ (insert s' (set (map source p)) ⊆ S') = (insert s (set (map target p)) ⊆ S')" by (induct p arbitrary: s; simp; blast)
  ultimately have allstatesinS' : "s ∈ S' ∧ (∀i< length p. target (p!i) ∈ S')" by (simp add: subset_iff assms)
  {
    assume assum1: "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ occurs A (fin p)"
    hence "∃ a ∈ A. a ∈ (set (map action p))" by simp
    then obtain a where assum2: "a ∈ A ∧ a ∈ (set (map action p))" by auto
    have "a ∈ (set (map action p)) ⟶ (∃i < length p. a = action (p!i))" by (induction p; auto)
    then obtain i where "i < length p ∧ a = action (p!i)" using assum2 by auto
    hence "validfinpath M s (take i p) (source (p!i)) ∧ (source (p!i), action (p!i), target (p!i)) ∈ transition M ∧ action (p!i) ∈ A ∧ target (p!i) ∈ S'" using assum1 assum2 allstatesinS' by auto
    hence "∃p' s'. validfinpath M s p' s' ∧ (∃a s''. (s', a, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ a ∈ A ∧ s'' ∈ S')" by blast
  }
  moreover {
    assume assum1: "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ occursstate S'' s (fin p)"
    hence "∃s' ∈ S''. s' ∈ insert s (set (map target p))" by simp
    then obtain s' where assum2: "s' ∈ S'' ∧ s' ∈ insert s (set (map target p))" by auto
    have "s' ∈ insert s (set (map target p)) ⟶ s' = s ∨ (∃i < length p. s' = target (p!i))" by (induction p; auto)
    hence "s' = s ∨ (∃i < length p. s' = target (p!i))" using assum2 by auto
    moreover have "s' = s ⟹ validfinpath M s [] s ∧ s ∈ S' ∩ S''"using assum2 assum1 allstatesinS' by auto
    moreover {
      assume "∃i < length p. s' = target (p!i)" 
      then obtain i where assum3 : "i < length p ∧ s'= target (p!i)" by auto
      hence "validfinpath M s (take i p) (source (p!i)) ∧ (source (p!i), action (p!i), target (p!i)) ∈ transition M" using assum1 by auto
      hence "validfinpath M s ((take i p) @ [(source (p!i), action (p!i), target (p!i))]) (target (p!i)) ∧ (target (p!i)) ∈ S''" using assum2 assum3 by simp
      moreover have "(target (p!i)) ∈ S'" using assum1 assum3 allstatesinS' by auto
      ultimately have "∃p' s'. validfinpath M s p' s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∩ S''" by blast
    }
    ultimately have "∃p' s'. validfinpath M s p' s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∩ S''" by blast
  }
  ultimately show ?thesis using assms by blast
qed

lemma addpathsnotoccurs: "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ validfinpath M s' p' s'' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p') ⟹ validfinpath M s (p @ p') s'' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin (p @ p'))"
  by auto       

lemma notemptypath : "s ∉ S' ∧ (occursstate S' s (fin p) ∨ occurs A (fin p)) ⟶ p ≠ []" 
  by (cases p; simp)

lemma existssplitpath :
  assumes "s ∈ S' ∧ (∀s ∈ S'. succ s ≠ [] ∧ laststate (succ s) ∈ S')" 
  shows "∃j s'. j < length (succ s') ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix i (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))"
  apply (induct i)
proof-
  have "succ s ≠ [] ⟹ recursiveconcpaths succ s = conc (succ s) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s)))" by (rule; simp)
  hence "0 < length (succ s) ∧ s ∈ S' ∧ suffix 0 (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop 0 (succ s)) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s)))" using assms by auto
  thus "∃j s'. j < length (succ s') ∧  s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix 0 (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))" by blast
next
  fix i
  assume "∃j s'. j < length (succ s') ∧  s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix i (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))"
  then obtain j s' where IH: "j < length (succ s') ∧  s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix i (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))" by auto
  have "suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = suffix (Suc 0) (suffix i (recursiveconcpaths succ s))" by auto
  moreover have "... = (conc (drop (Suc j) (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s'))))" using IH by auto
  ultimately have IH: "j < length (succ s') ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = (conc (drop (Suc j) (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s'))))" using IH by simp
  {
    assume assum2: "Suc j < length (succ s')"
    hence "∃j s'. j < length (succ s') ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))" using IH by auto
  }
  moreover {
    assume assum2: "Suc j ≥ length (succ s')"
    let ?s = "laststate (succ s')"
    have "suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = recursiveconcpaths succ ?s" using assum2 IH by auto
    moreover have "succ ?s ≠ [] ⟹ recursiveconcpaths succ ?s= conc (succ ?s) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ ?s)))" by (rule; simp)
    moreover have "succ ?s ≠ []" using assms IH by auto
    ultimately have "0 < length (succ ?s) ∧ suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (succ ?s) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ ?s)))" by simp
    moreover have "drop 0 (succ ?s) = succ ?s" by auto
    ultimately have "0 < length (succ ?s) ∧ ?s ∈ S' ∧ suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop 0 (succ ?s)) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ ?s)))" using assms IH by metis
    hence "∃j s'. j < length (succ s') ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))" by blast
  }
  ultimately show "∃j s'. j < length (succ s') ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ suffix (Suc i) (recursiveconcpaths succ s) = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))" using not_le_imp_less by auto
qed

lemma feasiblesublemma :
  assumes exclusive: "⋀s a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟹ s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e "
  and persistent: "⋀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟹ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  and feasible: "⋀s a. s ∈ S' ∧ a ∈ -B ⟹ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)))"
  and "finite (-B)"
  and "∃a ∈ -B. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  shows "s ∈ S' ⟹ ∃p s'. p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))"
proof-
  assume assum1 : "s ∈ S'"
  let ?L = "{a ∈ -B. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e}"
  have "∀n. ∀L. card L = n ∧ L ⊆ ?L ⟶ (∃p s'. (L ≠ {} ⟶ p ≠ []) ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p)))"
  proof
    fix n
    show "∀L. card L = n ∧ L ⊆ ?L ⟶ (∃p s'. (L ≠ {} ⟶ p ≠ []) ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p)))"
      apply (induct n; rule allI; rule impI)
    proof-
      let ?p = "[]"
      fix L 
      assume assum2 : "card L = 0 ∧ L ⊆ ?L"
      hence "L ⊆ (-B) ∧ finite (-B)" using assms(4) by auto
      hence "finite L" using finite_subset by auto
      hence "L = {}" using assum2 by auto
      hence "(L ≠ {} ⟶ ?p ≠ []) ∧ validfinpath M s ?p s ∧ s ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin []) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶  occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin ?p ) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin ?p))" using assum1 by auto
      thus "∃p s'. (L ≠ {} ⟶ p ≠ []) ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶  occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" by blast
    next
      fix n 
      fix L
      assume IH : "∀L. card L = n ∧ L ⊆ ?L ⟶ (∃p s'. (L ≠ {} ⟶ p ≠ []) ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶  occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p)))"
      assume "card L = Suc n ∧ L ⊆ ?L"
      then obtain a L' where assum2: "L = insert a L' ∧ a ∉ L' ∧ card L' = n ∧ L ⊆ ?L" using card_eq_SucD by metis
      then obtain p s' where assum3: "(L' ≠ {} ⟶ p ≠ []) ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L' ⟶  occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" using IH by blast
      have "(occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ∨ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" by auto
      moreover {
        assume "occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p)"
        (*if we have that B is not the entire set, do we need exclusive?*)
        hence "p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" using exclusive notemptypath assum2 assum3 by auto
        hence "∃p s'. p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" by auto
      }
      moreover {
        have sinpihon: "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e" using assum2 by blast
        assume assum4 : "¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)"
        moreover have ainBcomp : "a ∈ -B" using assum2 by auto
        ultimately obtain p' s'' where "validfinpath M s' p' s'' ∧ s'' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p') ∧ ((occurs (α_el a) (fin p') ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s' (fin p')))" using persistent assum3 feasible sinpihon by metis
        moreover then have "p' ≠ []" using ainBcomp assum3 assum4 exclusive notemptypath persistent sinpihon by metis
        moreover have "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s' (fin p') ⟹  occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (extendfinpath p (fin p'))" by (rule occursstaterightvalidpath)
        moreover have "occurs (α_el a) (fin p') ⟹ occurs (α_el a) (fin (p @ p'))" by auto
        ultimately have "p @ p' ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s (p @ p') s'' ∧ s'' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin (p @ p')) ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin (p @ p')) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin (p @ p')))" using assum3 by auto
        moreover have "∀a. a ∈ L' ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (extendfinpath p (fin p')) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p)" using assum3 occursstateleft by metis
        moreover then have "∀a. a ∈ L' ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin (p @ p')) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin (p @ p'))" by auto
        ultimately have "p @ p' ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s (p @ p') s'' ∧  s'' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin (p @ p')) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin (p @ p')) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin (p @ p')))" using assum2 assum3 by auto
        hence "∃p s'. p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" by blast
      }
      ultimately show "∃p s'. (L ≠ {} ⟶ p ≠ [])  ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" by blast
    qed
  qed
  moreover have "?L ≠ {}" using assms(5) by auto
  ultimately have  "∃p s'. p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ ?L ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" by blast
  thus ?thesis by auto
qed

lemma constructfairpath :
  assumes exclusive: "∀s. ∀a ∈ -B. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e "
  and persistent: "∀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟶ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  and reachable: "∀s ∈ S'. ∀a ∈ -B. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)))"
  and "finite (-B)"
  and "∀s ∈ S'. ∃a∈- B. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  shows "s ∈ S' ⟹ ∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p))))))"
proof-
  assume assum1: "s ∈ S'"
  have "∀s ∈ S'. ∃p. p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p (laststate p) ∧ laststate p ∈ S' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" 
  (is "∀s ∈ S'. ?P s")
  proof
    fix s
    assume "s ∈ S'"
    hence "∃p s'. p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" 
      apply (subst feasiblesublemma)
      using  exclusive persistent reachable assms(4) assms(5) apply blast+
      done
    then obtain p s' where "p ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ S' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin p))" by auto
    thus "?P s" using validfinpathlaststate by metis
  qed
  then obtain succ where assum2: "∀s' ∈ S'. succ s' ≠ [] ∧ validfinpath M s' (succ s') (laststate (succ s')) ∧ laststate (succ s') ∈ S' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin (succ s')) ∧ (∀a. a ∈ -B ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s' (fin (succ s')) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin (succ s')))" by metis
  let ?p = "recursiveconcpaths succ s"
  have validinfpath: "validinfpath M s ?p" using validinfpathconc assum1 assum2 by metis
  moreover have "¬ occurs α⇩f (inf ?p)" 
    apply (subst occursinfalternative) 
    apply (subst validpredconc [where ?P="λs. λt. action (t) ∉ α⇩f" and ?Q="λs. λp. ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p)"])
    using assum1 assum2 apply auto
    done
  moreover have "∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (?p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i ?p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (?p i)) (inf (suffix i ?p)))))"
    apply (rule ballI allI)+
  proof
    fix a i
    assume ainBcomp: "a ∈ -B"
    assume phion: "source (?p i) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
   (*opschonen*)
    obtain j s' where assum3: "s' ∈ S' ∧ j < length (succ s') ∧ suffix i ?p = conc (drop j (succ s')) (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s')))" using suffix_recursiveconcpaths assum1 assum2 by metis
    have "validinfpath M (source (?p i)) (suffix i ?p)" using validinfpath validinfsubpathright by metis
    moreover have "drop j (succ s') ≠ [] ∧ laststate (drop j (succ s')) = laststate (succ s')" using assum3 by auto
    ultimately have "validfinpath M (source (?p i)) (drop j (succ s')) (laststate (succ s'))" using validinfpathsplitlaststate assum3 by metis
    { 
      moreover assume "¬occurs (α_el a) (fin (drop j (succ s'))) ∧ ¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (?p i)) (fin (drop j (succ s')))"
      ultimately have "laststate (succ s') ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e" using persistent ainBcomp phion by metis
      hence "occurs (α_el a) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s')))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (laststate (succ s')) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s'))))" using ainBcomp assum2 assum3 by blast
    }
    hence "occurs (α_el a) (fin (drop j (succ s'))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (?p i)) (fin (drop j (succ s'))) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s')))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (laststate (succ s')) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s'))))" by blast
    hence "occurs (α_el a) (fin (drop j (succ s'))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (?p i)) (fin (drop j (succ s'))) ∨
       occurs (α_el a) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s')))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (laststate (succ s')) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s'))))" by blast
    moreover have "drop j (succ s') ≠ [] ∧ laststate (succ s') = laststate (drop j (succ s'))" using assum3 by auto
    ultimately have "occurs (α_el a) (extendfinpath (drop j (succ s')) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s'))))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (?p i)) (extendfinpath (drop j (succ s')) (fin (succ (laststate (succ s')))))" 
      using occursleft occursstateleft occursright occursstateright by metis
    hence res1: "occurs (α_el a) (fin (drop j (succ s') @ (succ (laststate (succ s'))))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (?p i)) (fin (drop j (succ s') @ (succ (laststate (succ s')))))" by simp
    have "inf (suffix i ?p) = extendfinpath (drop j (succ s')) (inf (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ s'))))" using assum3 by auto
    moreover have "succ (laststate (succ s')) ≠ []" using assum2 assum3 by auto    
    ultimately have "inf (suffix i ?p) = extendfinpath ((drop j (succ s')) @ (succ (laststate (succ s')))) (inf (recursiveconcpaths succ (laststate (succ (laststate (succ s'))))))" by (simp add: unfoldrecursiveconcpaths extendfinpath_extendfinpath)
    thus "occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i ?p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (?p i)) (inf (suffix i ?p))"  using occursleft occursstateleft res1 by metis
  qed
  ultimately show ?thesis by blast
qed

lemma infpathoccursoroccursstate : 
  assumes "validinfpath M s p ∧ (occurs A (inf p) ∨ occursstate S' s (inf p))"
  shows "∃i. source (p i) ∈ S' ∨ action (p i) ∈ A" 
  using assms ind.simps(2) occursinfalternative occursstatealternative validinfpath_def by metis

lemma theorem24_subformula :
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ (∀a. finite (α_el a)) ∧ finite (-B)"
  and "⋀a. ¬dependvar (φ_off a) M 0"
  and "⋀a. ¬dependvar (φ_on a) M 0"
  and invarinf: "⋀p s. validinfpath M s p ⟹ P s (inf p) =  (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p))))))"
  and locking: "⋀s. locked M B s = (∀ a ∈ -B. s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e)"
  and exclusive: "⋀s a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟹ s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e " 
  and persistent: "⋀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟹ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (φ_on a)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (and' (φ_off a) (var 0))) (Diamond (Acts ((α_el a) -α⇩f)) (var 0))))))⟧ M e
    = ((∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e))
  ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p)))"
  apply (simp add: assms del: Diamond.simps occurssimps locking)
  apply (subst lemma50)
  apply (simp add: assms)
  apply (simp add: assms)
  apply (subst notdependshiftdown)
  apply (simp add: assms)
proof
  assume "∃S'. S' ⊆ (⋂a∈- B. {s. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ (s' ∈ S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) ∨ (∃s'' a'. a' ∈ α_el a - α⇩f ∧ (s', a', s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ S')))}) ∧ s ∈ S'"
  then obtain S' where assum1: "S' ⊆ (⋂a∈- B. {s. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ (s' ∈ S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) ∨ (∃s'' a'. a' ∈ α_el a ∧ a' ∉ α⇩f ∧ (s', a', s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ S')))}) ∧ s ∈ S'" by auto
  let ?S' = "S' ∩ {s'. ∄p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s'' ∨ enabled M s'' α⇩e)}"
  have "∀s ∈ ?S'. ∀a ∈ -B. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)))"
    apply (rule ballI)+
  proof
    fix s a
    assume assum2: "s ∈ ?S'"
    hence "s ∈ S'" by auto
    moreover assume "a ∈ - B"
    moreover assume "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
    ultimately have "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ (s' ∈ S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) ∨ (∃s'' a'. a' ∈ α_el a ∧ a' ∉ α⇩f ∧ (s', a', s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ S'))" using assum1 by auto
    then obtain p s' where validpath: "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ (s' ∈ S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) ∨ (∃s'' a'. a' ∈ α_el a ∧ a' ∉ α⇩f ∧ (s', a', s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ S'))" using assum1 by presburger
    moreover have "enabled M s' α⇩e ⟹ False" using assum2 validpath by auto
    moreover {
      assume s'inS' : "s' ∈ S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e"
      moreover have "s' ∈ insert s (set (map target p))" using validpath by (subst sourcetargetfin[where ?s'=s']; auto)
      ultimately have "occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)" by auto
      moreover have "∄p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s'' ∨ enabled M s'' α⇩e)" 
      proof
        assume "∃p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s'' ∨ enabled M s'' α⇩e)"
        then obtain p' s'' where "validfinpath M s' p' s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p') ∧ (locked M B s'' ∨ enabled M s'' α⇩e)" by auto
        hence "validfinpath M s (p @ p') s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin (p @ p')) ∧ (locked M B s'' ∨ enabled M s'' α⇩e)" using validpath addpathsnotoccurs by metis
        thus False using assum2 by blast
      qed
      ultimately have "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)" using validpath s'inS' by auto
    }
    moreover {
      assume "∃s'' a'. a' ∈ α_el a ∧ a' ∉ α⇩f ∧ (s', a', s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ S'"
      then obtain a' s'' where s''inS': "a' ∈ α_el a ∧ a' ∉ α⇩f ∧ (s', a', s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ S'" by auto
      hence "validfinpath M s' [(s', a', s'')] s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin ([(s', a', s'')])) ∧ occurs (α_el a) (fin (p @ [(s', a', s'')]))" by auto
      hence validaddpath : "validfinpath M s (p @ [(s', a', s'')]) s'' ∧  ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin (p @ [(s', a', s'')])) ∧ occurs (α_el a) (fin (p @ [(s', a', s'')]))" using validpath validfinpathsplit addpathsnotoccurs by metis 
      moreover have "∄p s'. validfinpath M s'' p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e)" 
      proof
        assume "∃p s'. validfinpath M s'' p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e)"
        then obtain p' s''' where "validfinpath M s'' p' s''' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p') ∧ (locked M B s''' ∨ enabled M s''' α⇩e)" by auto
        hence "validfinpath M s ((p @ [(s', a', s'')]) @ p') s''' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin ((p @ [(s', a', s'')]) @ p')) ∧ (locked M B s''' ∨ enabled M s''' α⇩e)" using validaddpath addpathsnotoccurs by metis
        thus False using assum2 by blast
      qed
      ultimately have "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ occurs (α_el a) (fin p)" using s''inS' by blast
    }
    ultimately show "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p))" by blast
  qed
  moreover have "⋀s. s ∈ ?S' ⟹ ¬locked M B s" 
    apply (subgoal_tac "validfinpath M s [] s ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin [])")
    apply blast
    apply simp
    done
  ultimately have "s ∈ ?S' ⟹ ∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p))))))"
    apply (subst constructfairpath)
    using exclusive persistent assms(1) apply blast+
    using locking apply meson
    using persistent assms(1) apply blast+
    done
  hence "s ∈ ?S' ⟹ ∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p)" using invarinf by blast
  thus "((∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e))
  ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p)))" using assum1 by blast
next
  let ?S' = "{s. (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e))
  ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p))}"
  assume "(∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e))
  ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p))"
  hence "s ∈ ?S'" by simp
  moreover have "?S' ⊆ (⋂a∈- B. {s. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃s'' act. act ∈ α_el a - α⇩f ∧ (s', act, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ ?S')))})"
    apply (rule subsetI INT_I CollectI impI)+
  proof-
    fix s a
    assume assum1: "s ∈ ?S'"
    assume assum2 : "a ∈ -B"
    assume assum3 : "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e" 
    show "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃s'' act. act ∈ α_el a - α⇩f ∧ (s', act, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ ?S'))"
    proof-
      have "(∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e)) ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p))" using assum1 by auto
      moreover {
        assume "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e)"
        hence "(∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s') ∨ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ enabled M s' α⇩e)" by auto
        moreover {
          assume "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s'"
          then obtain p s' where assum4: "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s'" by auto
          moreover have "occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)"
            apply (rule ccontr)
            apply (subgoal_tac "s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e")
            using locking persistent assum2 assum3 assum4 apply blast+
            done
          ultimately have assum4: "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s' ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p))" by auto
(*staat dit al ergens anders*)
          moreover {
            assume "occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)"
            hence "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃ n ∈ indicespath (fin p). target (ind n (fin p)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e)" using occursstatealternative by metis
            hence "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃ n < length p. target (p!n) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e)" by simp
            moreover have "s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ⟹ validfinpath M s [] s ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin [])  ∧ s ∈ ?S' ∩ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e" using assum1 by simp
            moreover {
              assume "∃ n < length p. target (p!n) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e"
              then obtain n where "n < length p ∧ target (p!n) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e" by auto
              hence "validfinpath M (target (p!n)) (drop (Suc n) p) s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin (drop (Suc n) p)) ∧ locked M B s' ∧ validfinpath M s (take (Suc n) p) (target (p!n)) ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin (take (Suc n) p)) ∧ target (p!n) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e" 
                using assum4 validfinsubpathtargetright notoccursfinright notoccursfinleft validfinsubpathtarget by metis
              hence "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p)  ∧ s' ∈ ?S' ∩ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e" by auto
            }
            ultimately have "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p)  ∧ s' ∈ ?S' ∩ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e" by blast
          }
          moreover {
            assume "occurs (α_el a) (fin p)"
            then obtain n where "n < length p ∧ action (p!n) ∈ α_el a" using occursfinalternative by blast
            hence "validfinpath M (target (p!n)) (drop (Suc n) p) s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin (drop (Suc n) p)) ∧ locked M B s' ∧ validfinpath M s (take n p) (source (p!n)) ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin (take n p)) ∧ (source (p!n), action (p!n), target (p!n)) ∈ transition M ∧ action (p!n) ∈ α_el a ∧ action (p!n) ∉ α⇩f" 
              using assum4 validfinsubpath validfinsubpathtargetright notoccursfinright notoccursfinleft occursfinalternative ithtransitionfinpath splittransition by metis
            hence "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p)  ∧ (∃act s''. (s', act, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ act ∈ α_el a - α⇩f ∧ s'' ∈ ?S')" by blast
          }
        ultimately have "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ ((s' ∈ ?S' ∩ (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e)) ∨ (∃act s''. (s', act, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ act ∈ α_el a - α⇩f ∧ s'' ∈ ?S'))" 
          by meson
        }
        ultimately have "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃s'' act. act ∈ α_el a ∧ act ∉ α⇩f ∧ (s', act, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ ?S'))" by blast
      }
      moreover {
        assume "∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p)"
        then obtain p where predP: "validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p))))))" using invarinf by auto
        moreover from this have "source (p 0) = s ∧ suffix 0 p = p" by (simp add: validinfpath_def)
        ultimately have validinfpath: "validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (inf p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (inf p))" using assum2 assum3 by metis
        then obtain i where sourceoraction : "source (p i) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ action (p i) ∈ α_el a" using infpathoccursoroccursstate by metis
        have "⋀j. source (p j) ∈ ?S'"
        proof-
          fix j
          have "validinfpath M (source (p j)) (suffix j p) ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf (suffix j p)) ∧ P (source (p j)) (inf (suffix j p))"
          proof-
            have "(∀a ∈ -B. ((∀k. (source ((suffix j p) k)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix k (suffix j p))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source ((suffix j p) k)) (inf (suffix k (suffix j p)))))))" using predP by simp
            moreover have "validinfpath M (source (p j)) (suffix j p) ∧  ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf (suffix j p))" using predP by auto
            ultimately show ?thesis using invarinf by metis
          qed
          thus "source (p j) ∈ ?S'" by blast
        qed
        moreover have "target (p i) = source (p (Suc i))" using predP by (simp add: validinfpath_def)
        ultimately have "source (p i) ∈ ?S' ∧ target (p i) ∈ ?S'" by auto
        moreover have "validfinpath M s (prefix i p) (source (p i)) ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin (prefix i p)) ∧ action (p i) ∉ α⇩f" using validinfpath validinfsubpath by auto
        moreover have "(source (p i), action (p i), target (p i)) ∈ transition M" using validinfpath splittransition validinfpath_def by metis
        ultimately have "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (s' ∈ ?S' ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃s'' act. act ∈ α_el a ∧ act ∉ α⇩f ∧ (s', act, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ ?S'))" using sourceoraction by blast
      }
      ultimately show ?thesis by blast
    qed
  qed
  ultimately show "∃x. x ⊆ (⋂a∈- B. {s. s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (enabled M s' α⇩e ∨ s' ∈ x ∧ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e ∨ (∃s'' act. act ∈ α_el a - α⇩f ∧ (s', act, s'') ∈ transition M ∧ s'' ∈ x)))}) ∧ s ∈ x" by blast
qed

(*use both of these in previous lemma*)
lemma predPsubpathinf :
  assumes invarinf: "∀p s. validinfpath M s p ⟶ (P s (inf p) =  (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p)))))))"
  shows "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validinfpath M s' p' ∧ P s (inf (conc p p')) ⟹ P s' (inf p')"
proof-
  assume assum1 : "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validinfpath M s' p' ∧ P s (inf (conc p p'))"
  hence "validinfpath M s (conc p p') ∧ P s (inf (conc p p'))" by auto
  hence "∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source ((conc p p') (i + length p))) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix (i + length p) (conc p p'))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source ((conc p p') (i + length p))) (inf (suffix (i + length p) (conc p p'))))))" using invarinf by blast
  hence "∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p' i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p')) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p' i)) (inf (suffix i p')))))" by auto
  thus ?thesis using assum1 invarinf by metis  
qed

lemma predPsuperpathinf :
  assumes invarinf: "⋀p s. validinfpath M s p ⟹ (P s (inf p) =  (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p)))))))"
  and persistent: "⋀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟹ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  shows "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validinfpath M s' p' ∧ P s' (inf p') ⟹ P s (inf (conc p p'))"
proof-
  assume assum1 : "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validinfpath M s' p' ∧ P s' (inf p')"
  hence predPentirepath: "∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p' i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p')) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p' i)) (inf (suffix i p')))))" using invarinf by blast
  have "∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (conc p p' i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i (conc p p'))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (conc p p' i)) (inf (suffix i (conc p p'))))))"
    apply (rule ballI allI)+
  proof
    fix a i
    assume assum2 : "a ∈ -B"
    assume assum3 : "source (conc p p' i) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
    {
      assume assum4 : "i < length p"
      hence "validfinpath M (source (p ! i)) (drop i p) s' ∧ source (p' 0) = s'" using assum1 validfinsubpathright validinfpath_def by metis
      moreover have nonempty : "drop i p ≠ []" using assum4 by auto
      ultimately have "validfinpath M (source (p ! i)) (drop i p) (laststate (drop i p)) ∧ source (p' 0) = laststate (drop i p)" using validfinpathlaststate by metis
      moreover from this have "¬occurs (α_el a) (fin (drop i p)) ∧ ¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p!i)) (fin (drop i p)) ⟹ laststate (drop i p) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e" using assum2 assum3 assum4 conc_fst persistent by metis
      ultimately have "occurs (α_el a) (fin (drop i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p!i)) (fin (drop i p)) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix 0 p')) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (laststate (drop i p)) (inf (suffix 0 p'))" using assum2 predPentirepath by metis
      hence "occurs (α_el a) (fin (drop i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p!i)) (fin (drop i p)) ∨ occurs (α_el a) (inf p') ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (laststate (drop i p)) (inf p')" by auto
      hence "occurs (α_el a) (inf (conc (drop i p) p')) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p!i)) (inf (conc (drop i p) p'))" using extendfinpath.simps(2) nonempty occursstateleft occursleft occursright occursstateright by metis
      hence "occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i (conc p p'))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (conc p p' i)) (inf (suffix i (conc p p')))" using assum4 by auto  
    }
    moreover {
      assume assum4 : "i ≥ length p"
      hence "conc p p' i = p' (i - length p)" by auto
      hence "occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix (i - length p) p')) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p' (i - length p))) (inf (suffix (i - length p) p'))" using assum2 assum3 predPentirepath by auto
      hence "occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i (conc p p'))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (conc p p' i)) (inf (suffix i (conc p p')))" using assum4 by auto
    }
    moreover have "i < length p ∨ i ≥ length p" by auto
    ultimately show "occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i (conc p p'))) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (conc p p' i)) (inf (suffix i (conc p p')))" by blast
  qed
  moreover have "validinfpath M s (conc p p')" using assum1 by auto
  ultimately show ?thesis using invarinf by auto
qed

lemma predPsubpathsuperpathfin :
  assumes invarfin: "⋀p s s'. validfinpath M s p s' ⟹ locked M B s' = P s (fin p)"
  shows "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validfinpath M s' p' s'' ⟹ P s' (fin p') = P s (fin (p @ p'))"
  using invarfin validfinpathsplit by meson

lemma predPsubpathsuperpathinf :
  assumes invarinf: "⋀p s. validinfpath M s p ⟹ (P s (inf p) =  (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p)))))))"
  and persistent: "⋀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟹ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  shows "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validinfpath M s' p' ⟹ P s' (inf p') = P s (inf (conc p p'))"
  apply (rule iffI)
  apply (rule predPsuperpathinf [where ?φ_on=φ_on and ?φ_off=φ_off and ?α_el=α_el and ?e=e and ?B=B and ?M=M and ?p=p and ?s=s and ?s'=s'])
  prefer 4
  apply (rule predPsubpathinf [where ?φ_on=φ_on and ?φ_off=φ_off and ?α_el=α_el and ?e=e and ?B=B and ?M=M and ?p=p and ?s=s])
  using invarinf persistent apply blast+
  done

lemma predPsubpathsuperpath :
  assumes invarfin: "⋀p s s'. validfinpath M s p s' ⟹ P s (fin p) = locked M B s'"
  and invarinf: "⋀p s. validinfpath M s p ⟹ (P s (inf p) =  (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p)))))))"
  and persistent: "⋀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟹ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  shows "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validpath M s' p' ⟹ P s' p' = P s (extendfinpath p p')"
proof-
  assume assum1: "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validpath M s' p'"
  {
    fix fp
    assume assum2: "p' = fin fp"
    then obtain s'' where "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validfinpath M s' fp s''" using assum1 by auto
    hence "P s' (fin fp) = P s (fin (p @ fp))" by (subst predPsubpathsuperpathfin[where ?B=B and ?s''=s'']; auto simp: invarfin)
    hence "P s' p' = P s (extendfinpath p p')" using assum2 by simp
  }
  moreover {
    fix ip
    assume assum2: "p' = inf ip"
    hence "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validinfpath M s' ip" using assum1 by auto
    hence "P s' (inf ip) = P s (inf (conc p ip))" using invarinf persistent by (subst predPsubpathsuperpathinf[where ?φ_on=φ_on and ?φ_off=φ_off and ?α_el=α_el and ?e=e and ?B=B]; blast)
    hence "P s' p' = P s (extendfinpath p p')" using assum2 by simp
  }
  ultimately show ?thesis by (cases p')
qed

lemma notlocked : "s ∈ {s. ∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ locked M B s'} ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ⟹ s' ∈ {s. ∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ locked M B s'}"
  using validfinpathsplit by (simp; meson)

lemma feasible : 
  assumes invarinf: "⋀p s. validinfpath M s p ⟹ P s (inf p) =  ((∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p)))))))"
  and locking: "⋀s. locked M B s = (∀ a ∈ -B. s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e)"
  and exclusive: "⋀s a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟹ s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e " 
  and persistent: "⋀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟹ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  and feasiblesub: "⋀a s. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟹ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)))"
  and "finite (-B)"
  shows "(∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ locked M B s') ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ P s (inf p))"
proof-
  let ?S' = "{s. ∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ locked M B s'}"
  have "s ∈ ?S' ⟹ ∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬occurs {} (inf p) ∧ (∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p))))))"
    apply (subst constructfairpath [where ?S'="?S'"])
    using exclusive persistent apply blast+
    defer
    using assms(6) apply simp
    apply simp
    using locking validfinpath.simps(1) apply metis
    apply simp
    apply simp
    apply (rule ballI impI)+
  proof-
    fix s'' a
    assume assum1: "s'' ∈ ?S'"
    assume "a ∈ -B"
    moreover assume "s'' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
    ultimately obtain p s' where "validfinpath M s'' p s' ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s'' (fin p))" using feasiblesub by blast
    moreover from this have "s' ∈ ?S'" using assum1 by (subst notlocked [where ?s=s'' and ?p=p]; auto)
    ultimately show "∃p s'. validfinpath M s'' p s' ∧ s' ∈ ?S' ∧ ¬ occurs {} (fin p) ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s'' (fin p))" by (simp; blast)
  qed
  hence "s ∈ ?S' ⟹ ∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ P s (inf p)" using invarinf by blast
  thus ?thesis by auto
qed

theorem theorem24 :
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ (∀a. finite (α_el a)) ∧ finite (-B)"
  and "⋀a. ¬dependvar (φ_off a) M 0"
  and "⋀a. ¬dependvar (φ_on a) M 0"
  and invarfin: "⋀p s s'. validfinpath M s p s' ⟹  P s (fin p) = locked M B s'"
  and invarinf: "⋀p s. validinfpath M s p ⟹ P s (inf p) =  ((∀a ∈ -B. ((∀i. (source (p i)) ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟶ (occurs (α_el a) (inf (suffix i p)) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) (source (p i)) (inf (suffix i p)))))))"
  and locking: "⋀s. locked M B s = (∀ a ∈ -B. s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e)"
  and exclusive: "⋀s a. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟹ s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e " 
  and persistent: "⋀s p s' a. a ∈ -B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ∧ (¬occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)  ∧ ¬occurs (α_el a) (fin p)) ⟹ s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e"
  and reachable: "⋀a s. a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (φ_on a) 0⟧ M e ⟹ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (occurs (α_el a) (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (φ_off a) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p)))" 
  shows "s ∈ ⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (φ_on a)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (and' (φ_off a) (var 0))) (Diamond (Acts ((α_el a) -α⇩f)) (var 0))))))))⟧ M e =
  (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ P s p)"
  apply (subst negformula)
  apply (subst Diamondmatch)
  apply (subst theorem24_subformula; (rule assms; auto)?)
  apply (subst splitviolating_predicate)
proof-
  fix p p' s'
  show "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ validpath M s' p' ⟹ P s' p' = P s (extendfinpath p p')"
    by (subst predPsubpathsuperpath [where ?φ_on=φ_on and ?φ_off=φ_off and ?α_el=α_el and ?e=e and ?B=B and ?M=M and ?s=s and ?p = p]; (rule assms)?; auto)
next
  have "⋀s. (∃p. freeuntiloccurrence p α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ P s p) =
    ((∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e))
    ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s (inf p)))"
    apply (subst freeuntiloccurrenceprogressing_lockedenabled_pred) 
    apply (subst feasible [where ?φ_on=φ_on and ?φ_off=φ_off and ?α_el=α_el])
    using invarinf locking exclusive persistent reachable assms(1) apply blast+
    using invarinf persistent apply (subst predPsubpathsuperpathinf[where ?φ_on=φ_on and ?φ_off=φ_off and ?α_el=α_el and ?e=e and ?B=B]; blast)
    using invarfin apply blast+
    done
  thus "(∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ match ρ p ∧ ((∃p s''. validfinpath M s' p s'' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s'' ∨ enabled M s'' α⇩e)) ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s' p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ P s' (inf p)))) =
      (∄p p' s'. match ρ p ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ freeuntiloccurrence p' α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s' B p' ∧ P s' p')" by blast
qed

corollary corollary25 :
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ finite (-B)"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (diamond a tt)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (and' (box a ff) (var 0))) (Diamond (Acts ({a} - α⇩f)) (var 0))))))))⟧ M e =
  (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ WFA M B s p)"
  apply (rule theorem24)
  apply (simp add: assms notoccursnotdepends)+
  apply (simp add: WFAinvarfin)
  apply (simp only: WFAinvarinf)
  apply (simp add: locked_def; blast)
  apply simp
proof-
  fix a s
  assume "a ∈ - B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (diamond a tt) 0⟧ M e"
  then obtain s' where "(s, a, s') ∈ transition M" by auto
  hence "validfinpath M s [(s, a, s')] s' ∧ occurs {a} (fin [(s, a, s')])" by auto
  thus "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (occurs {a} (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (box a ff) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p))" by blast
next
  fix s p s' a
  assume "a ∈ - B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (diamond a tt) 0⟧ M e ∧ ¬ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (box a ff) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∧ ¬ occurs {a} (fin p)"
  hence "s' ∉ ⟦shiftdown (box a ff) 0⟧ M e" using notoccursendpath by metis
  thus "s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (diamond a tt) 0⟧ M e" by simp
qed

lemma lockedphion_WHFA: "finite (-B) ⟹ locked M B s = (∀a∈- B. s ∉ ⟦shiftdown (Diamond (Star (Acts (- B))) (diamond a tt)) 0⟧ M e)"
  apply (simp only: shiftdownDiamond shiftdownBox shiftdown.simps)
  apply (simp only: Diamondreachable)
proof-
  have "locked M B s = WHFA M B s (fin [])" by (simp only: WHFAempty)
  thus "locked M B s = (∀a∈- B. a ∉ reachableactions M B s)" by (auto simp: WHFA_def perpetuallyreachable_def)
qed

corollary corollary26 :
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ finite (-B)"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (Diamond (Star (Acts (-B))) (diamond a tt))) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (and' (Box (Star (Acts (-B))) (box a ff)) (var 0))) (Diamond (Acts ({a} - α⇩f)) (var 0))))))))⟧ M e =
  (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ WHFA M B s p)"
  apply (rule theorem24)
  apply (simp add: assms notoccursnotdepends)+
  apply (simp add: WHFAinvarfin)
  apply (simp only: WHFAinvarinf assms)
  apply (simp only: lockedphion_WHFA assms; simp)
  apply (simp only: shiftdownDiamond shiftdownBox shiftdown.simps)
  using Boxnotreachable Diamondreachable assms apply meson
proof-
  fix s p s' a
  assume "a ∈ - B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (Diamond (Star (Acts (- B))) (diamond a tt)) 0⟧ M e ∧ ¬ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (Box (Star (Acts (- B))) (box a ff)) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∧ ¬ occurs {a} (fin p)"
  hence "s' ∉ ⟦shiftdown (Box (Star (Acts (- B))) (box a ff)) 0⟧ M e" using notoccursendpath by meson
  hence "s' ∈ ⟦neg (Box (Star (Acts (- B))) (box a ff))⟧ M e" by simp
  moreover have "⟦neg (box a ff)⟧ M e = ⟦diamond a tt⟧ M e" by auto
  ultimately have "s' ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (- B))) (diamond a tt)⟧ M e" using negBox Diamond_eq by metis
  thus "s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (Diamond (Star (Acts (- B))) (diamond a tt)) 0⟧ M e" by simp
next
  fix a s
  assume "a ∈ - B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (Diamond (Star (Acts (- B))) (diamond a tt)) 0⟧ M e"
  hence "s ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (- B))) (diamond a tt)⟧ M e" by simp
  hence "a ∈ reachableactions M B s" by (simp only: Diamondreachable assms)
  then obtain p s' s'' where "validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (s', a, s'') ∈ transition M" by (auto simp: reachableactionsdef)
  hence "validfinpath M s (p@[(s', a, s'')]) s'' ∧ occurs {a} (fin (p@[(s', a, s'')]))" by simp
  thus "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (occurs {a} (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown (Box (Star (Acts (- B))) (box a ff)) 0⟧ M e) s (fin p))" by blast
qed

corollary corollary27 :
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ finite (-B) ∧ (∀a. finite {a'. ¬ con a a'})"
  and "concurrency M con"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (diamond a tt)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (Diamond (Acts ({a'. ¬ con a a'} - α⇩f)) (var 0))))))))⟧ M e =
  (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ JA M con B s p)"
proof-
  have "⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (diamond a tt)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (Diamond (Acts ({a'. ¬ con a a'} - α⇩f)) (var 0))))))))⟧ M e =
    ⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (diamond a tt)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (and' ff (var 0))) (Diamond (Acts ({a'. ¬ con a a'} - α⇩f)) (var 0))))))))⟧ M e"
    by (simp add: assms(1) Diamond_eq)
  moreover have "s ∈ ⟦neg (Diamond ρ (nu (And (-B) (λa. or (neg (diamond a tt)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (-α⇩f))) (or (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) (and' ff (var 0))) (Diamond (Acts ({a'. ¬ con a a'} - α⇩f)) (var 0))))))))⟧ M e =
  (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ JA M con B s p)"
  apply (rule theorem24)
  apply (simp add: assms notoccursnotdepends)+
  apply (simp add: JAinvarfin assms)
  apply (simp only: JAinvarinf)
  apply (simp add: locked_def; blast)
  apply simp
  proof-
    fix a s
    assume "a ∈ -B ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (diamond a tt) 0⟧ M e"
    then obtain s' where "(s, a, s') ∈ transition M" by auto
    moreover have "¬ con a a" using assms(2) by (simp add: concurrency_def)
    ultimately have "validfinpath M s [(s, a, s')] s' ∧ occurs {a'. ¬ con a a'} (fin [(s, a, s')])" by auto
    thus "∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ (occurs {a'. ¬ con a a'} (fin p) ∨ occursstate (⟦shiftdown ff 0⟧ M e) s (fin p))" by blast
  next
    fix s p s' a
    have "validfinpath M s p s' ⟶ enabledactions M s ∩ preimagerelation con (alloccurringactions (fin p)) ⊆ enabledactions M s'" using assms(2) by (auto simp: concurrency_def)
    moreover assume "a ∈ - B ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ s ∈ ⟦shiftdown (diamond a tt) 0⟧ M e ∧ ¬ occursstate (⟦shiftdown ff 0⟧ M e) s (fin p) ∧ ¬ occurs {a'. ¬ con a a'} (fin p)"
    ultimately have "a ∈ enabledactions M s'" by auto
    thus "s' ∈ ⟦shiftdown (diamond a tt) 0⟧ M e" by simp
  qed
  ultimately show ?thesis by blast
qed

lemma Diamondor : "⟦Diamond R (or f g)⟧ M e = ⟦or (Diamond R f) (Diamond R g)⟧ M e"
proof-
  have "⋀s. s ∈ ⟦Diamond R (or f g)⟧ M e = (s ∈ ⟦or (Diamond R f) (Diamond R g)⟧ M e)" by (auto simp: Diamondmatch)
  thus ?thesis by auto
qed

lemma freeenabledpath : 
  assumes "finite (- α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e"
  shows "s ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt) f)⟧ M e =
    (s ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) f⟧ M e ∨ 
       (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ enabled M s' α⇩e))" 
  apply (subst Diamondor)
proof-
  have "s ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt)⟧ M e = 
    (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ match (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) p ∧ s' ∈ ⟦Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt⟧ M e)" by (rule Diamondmatch)
  moreover have "... = (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ enabled M s' α⇩e)" by (subst Diamond_enabled matchstaract; simp add: assms)+
  ultimately show "(s ∈ ⟦formula.or (Diamond (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt)) (Diamond (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) f)⟧ M e) = 
    (s ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) f⟧ M e ∨ (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ enabled M s' α⇩e))" unfolding formulasemantics.simps by blast
qed

lemma SFAformula : 
  assumes "finite (-α⇩f) ∧ finite α⇩e ∧ finite (-B)"
  and feasible: "⋀s. (∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ locked M B s') ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ SFA M B s (inf p))"
  and subformula: "⋀s. s ∈ ⟦Diamond (Star (Acts (- α⇩f))) f⟧ M e =
        ((∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s')
        ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ SFA M B s (inf p)))" 
  shows "s ∈ ⟦neg (Diamond (Times ρ (Star (Acts (- α⇩f)))) (or (Diamond (Acts α⇩e) tt ) f))⟧ M e =
  (∄p. violating p ρ α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ SFA M B s p)"
  apply (subst negformula)
  unfolding Diamond.simps(5) apply (subst Diamondmatch)
  apply (subst splitviolating_predicate)
  apply (simp only: SFA_extendpath)
  apply (subst freeenabledpath)
  apply (simp add: assms)
  apply (subst subformula)
proof-
  have "⋀s. (∃p. freeuntiloccurrence p α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s B p ∧ SFA M B s p) =
    ((∃p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ (locked M B s' ∨ enabled M s' α⇩e))
    ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (inf p) ∧ SFA M B s (inf p)))"
    apply (rule freeuntiloccurrenceprogressing_lockedenabled_pred) 
    apply (rule feasible)
    apply (auto simp: SFA_extendpath)
    apply (simp only: SFAinvarfin)
    done
  thus "(∄p s'. validfinpath M s p s' ∧ match ρ p ∧ (((∃p s'a. validfinpath M s' p s'a ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ locked M B s'a) ∨ (∃p. validinfpath M s' p ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (path.inf p) ∧ SFA M B s' (path.inf p))) ∨ (∃p s'a. validfinpath M s' p s'a ∧ ¬ occurs α⇩f (fin p) ∧ enabled M s'a α⇩e))) = 
    (∄p p' s'. match ρ p ∧ validfinpath M s p s' ∧ freeuntiloccurrence p' α⇩f α⇩e ∧ progressing M s' B p' ∧ SFA M B s' p')" by blast
qed
